cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.CE 

This paper deals with information theory and communication systems, specifically the use of channel state information in a multiple-input-single-output broadcast channel. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). Other likely sub-categories include cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.MM (Multimedia), and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
